There's an extra space here, that breaks the lint.
I think you can do a one line to occupy less space, similar to `SteadyClock::duration ScanningDuration()`:

```c++
    /** Outpoint is spent if any non-conflicted transaction spends it */
    bool IsSpent(const COutPoint& outpoint) const EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(cs_wallet) { return HowSpent(outpoint) != SpendType::UNSPENT; }
```

